# v0.5.0 — 2026-06-10 — benoitcayladbx

## Fix #48: R2RML relationship URIs use the class label instead of the entity name

**Context**: GitHub issue [#48](https://github.com/databrickslabs/ontobricks/issues/48). In the
Digital Twin graph view, relationships between entities were never rendered in Filter → Expand
mode: only `rdf:type` assertions and datatype-property triples came back, and the BFS expansion
reported `expanded_count == initial_count` (no neighbours discovered). Root cause was a URI
namespace mismatch in the R2RML generator. `_add_entity_mapping` builds entity subject URIs from
the **local name of the ontology class URI** (`{base}{localName}/{id}`), whereas
`_resolve_class_name` — used by `_add_relationship_mapping` for the subject/object templates —
prioritised the **`ontology_class_label`**. When a class label differs from the local name of its
class URI, entity triples and relationship triples were written to two different URI namespaces and
were therefore never linked in the graph.

**Changes**:
1. `src/back/core/w3c/r2rml/R2RMLGenerator.py` — extracted a single shared helper
   `_entity_uri_name(class_uri, class_label, table)` that reproduces the entity subject-URI naming
   rule (local name of the class URI, else label, else table) as the **single source of truth** for
   the class-name segment of an entity URI. `_add_entity_mapping` now calls it (replacing the inline
   duplicate). `_resolve_class_name` now, for a matched entity, returns `_entity_uri_name(...)` using
   the matched entity's own `ontology_class` / `ontology_class_label` / table — guaranteeing the
   relationship subject/object URIs land byte-for-byte in the same namespace as the entity URIs. The
   former Priority 1 (entity label first) was the bug and is removed; the no-entity-matched fallback
   path (resolved URI → config label → class URI → table) is preserved unchanged.
2. `tests/units/mapping/test_r2rml_generator.py` — added
   `test_relationship_uris_match_entity_uris_when_label_differs`, a regression test for #48 where the
   class URI local names (`Cust`, `Ord`) deliberately differ from the labels (`Customer`, `Order`).
   It asserts that both entity and relationship templates use the `Cust`/`Ord` namespace and that the
   label namespace (`Customer/`, `Order/`) never appears.

**Modified files**:
- `src/back/core/w3c/r2rml/R2RMLGenerator.py`
- `tests/units/mapping/test_r2rml_generator.py`

**Test result**: `python -m pytest tests/units` -> **2266 passed, 15 skipped**. Targeted
`tests/units/mapping tests/units/dtwin` -> 262 passed. (`tests/property` skipped: `hypothesis` not
installed in this env — nightly-only.)

## UI: replace all grey backgrounds with white across the front app

**Context**: Requested change to drop the grey surface palette and make every background
white throughout the frontend — page shell, cards/panels, section/card headers, tab strips,
toolbars, hover surfaces, the breadcrumb, and the OntoViz canvas. Borders, status/semantic
tints (success/danger/info), scrollbar thumbs, interaction overlays (`rgba(0,0,0,.1/.15)`)
and disabled/read-only input cues (`#e9ecef !important`) were intentionally left intact so
contrast and affordances survive on a white surface.

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/static/global/css/main.css` — flipped the page-background token
   `--db-light-gray` from `#F7F7F7` to `#FFFFFF`; added `--db-bg-secondary: #FFFFFF`
   (previously always fell back to grey); forced the Bootstrap surface tokens
   `--bs-light` / `--bs-light-rgb` / `--bs-secondary-bg` / `--bs-tertiary-bg` to white so
   every `var(--bs-light, …)` etc. resolves white.
2. `src/front/static/global/ontoviz/css/ontoviz-variables.css` — `--ovz-bg-surface` and
   `--ovz-bg-overlay` set to `#ffffff`; the subtle grey `--ovz-entity-header-bg` gradient
   flattened to `#ffffff`.
3. Swept every hardcoded grey surface background (`#f8f9fa`, `#fafafa`, `#f5f5f5`,
   `#f1f3f5`, `#f9fafb`, `#fafbfc`, `#f8fafc`, `#f1f5f9`, `#f0f1f2`, `#f3f4f6`, non-`!important`
   `#e9ecef` / `#f0f0f0`, translucent `rgba(248,249,250,…)`, and grey-only `linear-gradient`s)
   to white across ~30 area CSS files and the inline `style="…background…"` strings in a few
   JS/HTML templates. Only `background` / `background-color` declarations were touched —
   borders, `fill`, chart data colours, and `!important` disabled cues were preserved.

**Modified files** (CSS unless noted):
- `src/front/static/global/css/main.css`, `components.css`, `pages.css`, `config.css`,
  `help-modal.css`, `mapping.css`, `ontology.css`, `query.css`
- `src/front/static/global/ontoviz/css/ontoviz-variables.css`, `ontoviz-ui.css`,
  `src/front/static/global/ontoviz/index.html`
- `src/front/static/{ontology,mapping,query,registry,domain}/css/*.css` (assistant,
  business-rules, groups, map, shared-panels, swrl, wizard; mapping design/diagnostics/
  manual/shared; query api/chat/sigmagraph/sync/visualization; registry / registry-teams;
  domain review/validation)
- inline styles: `ontology/js/ontology-shared-panels.js`, `ontology/js/ontology-wizard.js`,
  `domain/js/domain-documents.js`, `global/js/uc-location-widget.js`,
  `query/js/query-ontology-viewer.js`

**Test result**: CSS/HTML-only change. `pytest --ignore=tests/property` -> **2749 passed,
53 skipped, 16 failed**; the 16 failures are pre-existing backend API/e2e tests
(review-endpoints async-await harness, dtwin sync, home validation, set_version_status) with
no relation to frontend styling. `tests/property` skipped (`hypothesis` not installed).
No new lint errors on the edited assets.

## UI fixup: regressions from the all-white sweep (slider track + graph chat)

**Context**: After the grey→white sweep above, two regressions surfaced (verified against the
running dev server on `:8000`): (1) the Knowledge Graph **Depth slider** track became invisible,
and (2) the **Graph Chat** panel kept a grey gradient background. The home-page report ("sections
still grey") was a stale browser cache — `curl :8000/static/global/css/main.css` confirmed
`--db-light-gray: #FFFFFF` is served, so the home tiles (`.stat-item` / `.info-card` /
`.domain-btn` / `.quick-link*` / `.domain-status`, all `var(--db-light-gray)`) already render
white; the `?v=asset_version` cache-buster only changes on server restart.

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/static/global/css/main.css` — removed the global `--bs-secondary-bg` and
   `--bs-tertiary-bg` white overrides. Bootstrap's `.form-range` track and disabled-control
   surfaces read `--bs-secondary-bg`, so whitening it hid the slider line on the white page.
   Kept `--bs-light` / `--bs-light-rgb` white (drives `.bg-light` utilities to white, which the
   sweep intended); all `var(--bs-tertiary-bg, …)` background usages were already flattened to
   literal `#ffffff` in the sweep, so dropping that override is background-safe. Added a comment
   documenting why these two tokens must not be whitened.
2. `src/front/static/query/css/query-chat.css` — `--gc-panel-bg` changed from
   `linear-gradient(180deg, #f8fafc 0%, #eef2f7 100%)` to `#ffffff`. The original sweep only
   matched `background` / `background-color` declarations, so this grey lived in a CSS custom
   property and slipped through. `--gc-bot-border: #e9ecef` is a border and was left intact.

**Modified files**:
- `src/front/static/global/css/main.css`
- `src/front/static/query/css/query-chat.css`

**Test result**: CSS-only change; no new lint errors. Verified live via
`curl :8000/static/...` that the served CSS no longer overrides `--bs-secondary-bg` (slider track
visible again) and that the chat panel background is `#ffffff`. Browser hard-refresh / dev-server
restart needed to bust the cached `?v=` stylesheet.

## UI: light-grey navbar + monochrome (dark-grey) accent replacing Databricks Red

**Context**: Follow-up to the all-white theme. Requested: (1) top banner/navbar from black to a
classic light Databricks grey with black text; (2) navbar dropdown menus to use that same grey,
with a dark-grey hover instead of red; (3) globally, the red "highlight" buttons (e.g. the Home
page CTAs) to become dark grey.

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/static/global/css/main.css` — repointed the whole `--db-primary*` accent family
   from Databricks Red to a dark-grey palette (`--db-primary: #495057`, `-dark: #3a4046`,
   `-darker: #2b3035`, `-light: rgba(73,80,87,0.1)`, `-rgb: 73,80,87`). This is the single global
   lever: every token-based red (Home `.card-action` / `.step-badge` / `.domain-btn:hover` /
   `.quick-link*:hover`, `.bg-primary` / `.text-primary` / `.border-primary`, workflow step
   circles, tab underline, focus ring, navbar dropdown hover/active) is now dark grey.
2. `src/front/static/global/css/main.css` — added navbar chrome tokens
   (`--db-navbar-bg: #ECECEC`, `--db-navbar-border: #D8D8D8`) and restyled the navbar:
   light-grey background with a bottom border; brand + all `.nav-link`s (incl. the right-side
   bell / hourglass / help / gear / warehouse icons, which are `.nav-link`s) set to `--db-text`
   (black); `.nav-link:hover` / `.active` use the dark-grey accent (active also bold). Dropdown
   menus (incl. hover-flyout submenus) now use `--db-navbar-bg` with `--db-text` items,
   `--db-text-muted` headers, `--db-navbar-border` dividers, and a lighter shadow; hover/active
   items use the dark-grey accent with white text.
3. `src/front/templates/base.html` — navbar class `navbar-dark` → `navbar-light` so the
   Bootstrap collapse toggler icon renders dark on the light background.

**Out of scope (left red, by design)**: Bootstrap `bg-danger` notification count pills in the
navbar (semantic), and the self-contained Graph Chat / Ontology Assistant red theme (send button,
user bubbles, entity-link hovers, FAB, focus rings, shadows — dozens of hardcoded `#FF3621` /
`rgba(255,54,33,…)` refs). These can be converted to grey too on request.

**Modified files**:
- `src/front/static/global/css/main.css`
- `src/front/templates/base.html`

**Test result**: CSS/template-only change; no new lint errors. Verified live via
`curl :8000/static/global/css/main.css` that `--db-primary: #495057` and the navbar uses
`--db-navbar-bg`. Dev-server restart / hard refresh needed to bust the cached `?v=` stylesheet.

## UI fixup: navbar menu labels white on the light banner

**Context**: After the light-grey navbar change, the top-level menu labels (Registry, Domain,
Digital Twin) stayed white and unreadable. Root cause: each label span carried Bootstrap's
`.text-light` utility, which resolves through `--bs-light` (set to white in the all-white sweep),
overriding the black `.nav-link` colour.

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/templates/base.html` — removed `text-light` from the two navbar menu-label spans
   (`#currentDomainName` and the generic `{{ menu.label }}` span) so they inherit the black
   `.nav-link` colour and follow its hover/active (dark-grey) states. Kept `.small`.
2. `src/front/templates/base.html` + `src/front/static/global/css/main.css` — recoloured the
   process-chevron separators between menu items (were `stroke="rgba(255,255,255,0.5)"`, invisible
   on the light banner). The SVG `polyline` now uses `stroke="currentColor"` and
   `.navbar .nav-chevron` sets `color: var(--db-primary)`, so the chevrons render in the dark-grey
   accent and stay token-driven.

**Modified files**:
- `src/front/templates/base.html`
- `src/front/static/global/css/main.css`

**Test result**: Template/CSS-only change; no lint impact. Hard refresh / dev-server restart
needed to pick up the changes.

