## UI: unify every inline spinner on the OntoBricks brand spinner

**Context**: The app mixed two loading indicators — the OntoBricks branded SVG spinner
(rings + diamond, used in a handful of panels/overlays) and Bootstrap's plain
`.spinner-border` ring (used in ~60 templates/JS files, hundreds of call sites,
including button loading states and JS-generated markup). Requested: the OntoBricks
spinner everywhere.

**Approach**: Instead of editing every call site (risky across hundreds of varied
markup snippets, many built in JS strings), unify with a CSS-only override plus a
self-animating SVG. This covers all existing *and* future spinners with zero markup
changes.

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/static/global/img/loading-spinner.svg` — added a SMIL
   `<animateTransform type="rotate" .../>` to the node-ring group so the file
   self-animates when referenced as `<img>` or as a CSS `background-image`
   (the previous animation lived only in `main.css` and didn't apply to the file).
2. `src/front/static/global/css/main.css` — global override repainting every
   Bootstrap `.spinner-border` / `.spinner-grow` as the brand spinner:
   `border: 0`, `border-radius: 0`, `animation: none`,
   `background: url(/static/global/img/loading-spinner.svg) center / contain no-repeat`
   (all `!important` to beat Bootstrap's single-class rules), `color: transparent`,
   `vertical-align: -0.18em`. Bootstrap's own `width/height` (2rem; `-sm` = 1rem) are
   preserved, so size at each call site is unchanged. Left `.spin-animation`
   (rotating *status* icon for running tasks) untouched — it's not a loading spinner.

**Modified files**:
- `src/front/static/global/img/loading-spinner.svg`
- `src/front/static/global/css/main.css`

**Test result**: `pytest --ignore=tests/property` → 2749 passed, 53 skipped, 16 failed.
All failures are pre-existing backend API/E2E async issues (review endpoints,
set-version-status, dtwin/home API flows) unrelated to this CSS/SVG change; property
tests skipped (no `hypothesis` in env). Verified the SVG (with `animateTransform`) and
the CSS override are served by the dev server. Hard refresh / dev-server restart needed
to pick up the change.

